<item>
            <title>[SPARK-12340] overstep the bounds of Int in SparkPlan.executeTake</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-12340</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Reproduce&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   sql e.g.  select * from talbe1 where c1 = &apos;abc&apos; limit 2147483638&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   n will be 2147483638 in SparkPlan.executeTake(n: Int). If the first partition just have one row ( buf.size will be one), the result of  cod e numPartsToTry = (1.5 * n * partsScanned / buf.size).toInt will be Int.MaxValue. Then math.min(partsScanned + numPartsToTry, totalParts) will be Int.MinValue (-2147483648) .&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Exception&lt;/p&gt;

